Key Match Events: Weston Wilson drove in the tiebreaking run with an infield single down the third-base line, and the Philadelphia Phillies beat the Tampa Rays 3-2 on Wednesday night to complete a three-game sweep.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Philadelphia Phillies completed a three-game sweep of the Tampa Bay Rays.
The game was played at Citizens Bank Park in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, with an attendance of 40,715.
Zack Wheeler pitched 6.0 innings, allowing 4 hits, 2 earned runs, and striking out 9 batters for the Phillies.
Shane Baz pitched 5.1 innings, allowing 3 hits, 2 earned runs, and striking out 4 batters for the Rays.
